WEBVTT

00:00.334 --> 00:06.438
♪ Somewhere there's speaking ♪
[ Indistinct conversations ]

00:06.440 --> 00:10.576
♪ Oh, and it's rising
at the back of your mind ♪

00:10.578 --> 00:14.446
♪ You never could get it ♪

00:14.448 --> 00:16.582
♪ Unless you were fed it ♪

00:16.584 --> 00:18.350
♪ Now you're here ♪

00:18.352 --> 00:22.054
♪ And you don't know why ♪
[ Door opens ]

00:22.056 --> 00:26.625
♪ But under skinned knees
and the skid marks ♪

00:26.627 --> 00:27.960
[ Cellphone clicks ]

00:27.962 --> 00:30.329
♪ Past the places
where you used to learn ♪

00:30.331 --> 00:31.864
[ Cellphone beeps ]

00:31.866 --> 00:33.932
♪ You howl and listen ♪

00:33.934 --> 00:36.902
♪ Listen and wait for ♪

00:36.904 --> 00:40.973
♪ The echoes of angels
who won't return ♪

00:40.975 --> 00:43.742
♪ He's everything you want ♪
Mwah!

00:43.744 --> 00:47.079
♪ He's everything you need ♪
Uh-huh.

00:47.081 --> 00:48.680
Man: She's late, huh?

00:48.682 --> 00:51.050
Met online,
asked her to dinner?

00:51.052 --> 00:52.818
♪ He says
all the right things ♪

00:52.820 --> 00:54.186
[ Scoffs ] Yeah.
Why?

00:54.188 --> 00:56.789
You picked a great venue,
but just for drinks.

00:56.791 --> 00:59.491
It's all women want on
a first date with someone new,

00:59.493 --> 01:00.692
drinks or coffee --

01:00.694 --> 01:02.261
kind of
an unspoken rule.

01:02.263 --> 01:04.029
Oh, I didn't know that.

01:04.031 --> 01:06.598
I'll go get you another
club soda before my shift ends.

01:06.600 --> 01:07.866
Thank you.

01:07.868 --> 01:11.303
[ Indistinct conversations
continue ]

01:11.305 --> 01:15.407
♪♪

01:15.409 --> 01:17.676
♪ You're waiting for someone ♪

01:17.678 --> 01:19.078
♪ To put you together ♪

01:19.080 --> 01:20.479
[ Pen clicks ]

01:20.481 --> 01:21.780
♪ You're waiting for someone ♪

01:21.782 --> 01:24.650
♪ To push you away ♪

01:36.764 --> 01:38.230
Want me to close you out?

01:38.232 --> 01:39.565
I'm afraid so.

01:49.310 --> 01:50.776
Hey.

01:54.215 --> 01:55.914
Are you working?

01:56.884 --> 01:59.651
Have a good night, then.

01:59.653 --> 02:02.321
Might be for the best,
buddy.

02:02.323 --> 02:04.389
Some of the gals
you meet online these days

02:04.391 --> 02:05.858
are a little crazy.

02:05.860 --> 02:07.993
It can't be any worse
than my last date.

02:07.995 --> 02:08.994
[ Sighs ]

02:12.199 --> 02:17.569
[ Indistinct conversations
continue ]

02:17.571 --> 02:21.673
♪♪

02:22.810 --> 02:25.711
[ Indistinct radio chatter ]

02:27.414 --> 02:29.181
Flynn: I know.

02:29.183 --> 02:31.850
Okay, victim's name
is Drew Hudson,

02:31.852 --> 02:34.153
a D1 from Sex Crimes.

02:34.155 --> 02:35.420
Provenza: No.

02:35.422 --> 02:38.157
The roll-out didn't say anything
about a dead cop.

02:38.159 --> 02:39.992
Yeah, well, obviously Taylor
wants to keep it quiet

02:39.994 --> 02:43.028
while we determine if Hudson
had integrity challenges.

02:43.030 --> 02:44.263
Sykes:
And his supervisor --

02:44.265 --> 02:45.831
who says
Hudson was on vacation --

02:45.833 --> 02:47.499
is heading downtown
to brief the Captain.

02:47.501 --> 02:49.234
Let's not
jump to conclusions.

02:49.803 --> 02:51.069
Since when?

02:51.071 --> 02:52.804
Just because
the guy is black --

02:52.806 --> 02:54.640
Uh, we found enough drugs
in his body

02:54.642 --> 02:55.941
to imply
intent to distribute,

02:55.943 --> 02:58.710
but tell Patrice
she's doing a good job

02:58.712 --> 03:00.345
with your
sensitivity training.

03:00.915 --> 03:03.882
Body is down this way.

03:06.987 --> 03:09.288
The pool guy showed up for
his weekly cleaning this morning

03:09.290 --> 03:10.956
and saw Hudson's body
through the window.

03:10.958 --> 03:13.825
Almost 20 stab wounds
from a large knife,

03:13.827 --> 03:14.927
mostly in the back.

03:14.929 --> 03:16.628
Well,
this<i> is</i> Hollywood.

03:16.630 --> 03:18.096
T.O.D., Kendall?

03:18.098 --> 03:20.299
Say...an hour either side
of midnight.

03:20.301 --> 03:22.301
Didn't even pull his gun
from his holster.

03:22.303 --> 03:24.269
How do you get a drop
on a cop like this?

03:24.271 --> 03:25.671
Provenza: Well,
maybe he was high.

03:25.673 --> 03:26.772
What kind of drugs
did he have?

03:26.774 --> 03:28.373
Crystal meth.

03:28.375 --> 03:30.576
Might have been
lifting evidence
from the locker.

03:30.578 --> 03:32.144
Hmm.
Some kind of ligature

03:32.146 --> 03:34.313
on the front
of the guy's ankles --

03:34.315 --> 03:36.014
Not sure what that is.

03:36.016 --> 03:38.850
What is Mike doing
out there?

03:38.852 --> 03:40.752
[ Horn honks in distance ]

03:40.754 --> 03:41.920
He thinks
he's been here before.

03:41.922 --> 03:44.289
When -- a previous life?

03:44.291 --> 03:45.824
Uh, Lieutenant?

03:45.826 --> 03:47.659
There are little holes
near the bottom

03:47.661 --> 03:49.795
of both sides
of this doorway.

03:49.797 --> 03:52.531
It's gone now,
but someone strung a tripwire.

03:52.533 --> 03:54.066
Oh.

03:54.068 --> 03:57.436
Ah. So, when Hudson fell down,
someone jumped on him.

03:57.438 --> 04:00.372
So whoever killed Hudson
was waiting for him.

04:00.374 --> 04:03.642
Uh, whose place is this, anyway?
Where are they?

04:03.644 --> 04:04.943
There's no food
in the refrigerator.

04:04.945 --> 04:07.512
Empty closets,
no pictures, no dishes.

04:07.514 --> 04:11.350
Provenza: Okay, this is
going to be a massive
print and collection job,

04:11.352 --> 04:12.751
and if our cop was high --

04:12.753 --> 04:13.819
Uh, he wasn't, sir.

04:13.821 --> 04:15.020
I saw him last night

04:15.022 --> 04:16.488
at the bar
in the Fontenot Hotel.

04:16.490 --> 04:17.889
But I spoke to him.

04:17.891 --> 04:19.625
He looked at me like,
"Don't blow my cover."

04:19.627 --> 04:21.159
He was working
on something, sir.

04:21.161 --> 04:22.728
Not according
to his supervisor.

04:22.730 --> 04:26.999
And what were<i> you</i> doing
at the Fontenot Hotel?

04:27.001 --> 04:29.768
Um...I was
being stood up again.

04:29.770 --> 04:31.236
Tao: I got it!

04:31.238 --> 04:34.940
This is where the cartel leaders
met up with the FBI.

04:34.942 --> 04:37.276
What? Hudson was connected
to the cartel?

04:37.278 --> 04:39.411
How do you figure that?
No, no, no.

04:40.047 --> 04:41.647
You see this barcode?

04:41.649 --> 04:44.516
It means that all this furniture
came from a property house.

04:44.518 --> 04:47.486
This place is designed to be
a rental for film locations.

04:47.488 --> 04:51.189
We shot an episode
of "Badge of Justice" here

04:51.191 --> 04:53.759
back in season one.
Oh, my God.

04:53.761 --> 04:55.927
I didn't recognize this place...
"Badge," "Badge,"
"Badge."

04:55.929 --> 04:57.362
...because it's
been redecorated.

04:57.364 --> 05:00.866
We had more of a neo-Palladian
vibe going on.

05:00.868 --> 05:04.603
Anyway, I texted
BOJ's location manager,

05:04.605 --> 05:08.106
and she says the house is
represented by a service,

05:08.108 --> 05:10.008
and the company
set to film here

05:10.010 --> 05:12.277
is called
18 and Out Entertainment.

05:12.279 --> 05:15.714
So, how did
a murdered detective

05:15.716 --> 05:18.450
become the star
of their show?

05:22.189 --> 05:24.156
Valdez: Well, this was not
your average film company.

05:24.158 --> 05:27.259
Their CEO, Bo McClaren,
is a famous porn star,

05:27.261 --> 05:29.294
and his brand
is Barely Legal.

05:29.296 --> 05:32.030
He has sex with girls
the minute they turn 18,

05:32.032 --> 05:33.598
and he films it.

05:33.600 --> 05:35.133
Uh, here he is.

05:35.135 --> 05:38.470
His website's called
finallyfairgame.com.

05:38.472 --> 05:40.772
Sharon: Ugh.
Auditions girls
from all over the country.

05:40.774 --> 05:43.108
Detective, I take it
that you are checking

05:43.110 --> 05:45.277
to see if any of those
young women are underage.

05:45.279 --> 05:47.746
Or if Bo was maybe
"rehearsing" with them

05:47.748 --> 05:49.114
before their birthdays,

05:49.116 --> 05:50.782
but couldn't prove it.

05:50.784 --> 05:52.984
Taylor: Any chance this Bo guy
resented your investigation

05:52.986 --> 05:54.653
and took it out
on Hudson?

05:54.655 --> 05:56.088
I doubt it.

05:56.090 --> 05:57.989
When we had no luck
on the underage-sex front,

05:57.991 --> 05:59.257
we passed the case
on to Narco,

05:59.259 --> 06:00.726
thought they might
have a better chance

06:00.728 --> 06:01.960
getting Bo
on a drug charge,

06:01.962 --> 06:03.028
and we moved on.

06:03.030 --> 06:04.429
Well,<i> Hudson</i> didn't.

06:04.431 --> 06:06.698
I just found all this stuff
in his apartment --

06:06.700 --> 06:08.800
fresh notes
on McClaren,

06:08.802 --> 06:11.002
interviews with someone
named "Juliet"

06:11.004 --> 06:12.270
dated this month.

06:12.272 --> 06:13.672
It's not clear
if he was working the case

06:13.674 --> 06:14.940
or the girl, ma'am.

06:14.942 --> 06:17.642
Does the "Juliet"
mean something to you?

06:17.644 --> 06:19.311
No, not that
I can think of.

06:19.313 --> 06:22.147
Uh-huh.
So, tell me, Valdez,

06:22.149 --> 06:25.050
this vacation that
Hudson was supposedly on --

06:25.052 --> 06:26.518
Was it planned?

06:26.520 --> 06:27.853
Not exactly.

06:27.855 --> 06:29.621
Four days ago,
he asked for the week off.

06:31.525 --> 06:33.992
Look, he needed
some personal leave --

06:33.994 --> 06:35.360
doesn't make him
a bad cop.

06:35.362 --> 06:37.028
Provenza: No,
what makes him a bad cop

06:37.030 --> 06:40.232
are the 20 grams of meth
we found on his body.

06:40.234 --> 06:41.500
Meth?
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

06:41.502 --> 06:43.168
Nobody mentioned
any drugs here.

06:43.170 --> 06:45.837
No one's mentioning it again
outside of this room

06:45.839 --> 06:48.106
until we know
for an absolute certainty

06:48.108 --> 06:50.375
how it connects
to an L.A.P.D. officer.

06:50.377 --> 06:51.943
Well, Hudson used to work
in Narco.

06:51.945 --> 06:53.145
Maybe he used
those contacts.

06:53.147 --> 06:54.446
No, no, no.
I knew Drew.

06:54.448 --> 06:55.547
He wasn't dirty.

06:55.549 --> 06:57.416
He was a great cop
and a great human being.

06:57.418 --> 06:59.050
I personally
will vouch for him --

06:59.052 --> 07:03.588
Detective,
however you feel about Hudson,

07:03.590 --> 07:06.158
he was still involved somehow,
one way or the other,

07:06.160 --> 07:07.392
with Bo McClaren.

07:07.394 --> 07:09.961
Captain, we have prepped
a security video

07:09.963 --> 07:11.730
from the hotel bar.

07:11.732 --> 07:15.767
Andy, would you please
invite our famous young
porn star in for a chat?

07:15.769 --> 07:17.369
This way, please.

07:17.371 --> 07:21.072
And let me know
when my visitor arrives.

07:21.074 --> 07:22.774
[ Door opens ]

07:22.776 --> 07:24.743
[ Clears throat ]
So...

07:24.745 --> 07:28.647
We're all going to get to see
how you dress for a date.

07:29.683 --> 07:34.152
Detective Drew Hudson
enters the bar at 7:27 alone

07:34.154 --> 07:35.954
about 20 minutes
before Julio.

07:35.956 --> 07:36.988
Fast-forward, Buzz.

07:36.990 --> 07:38.190
[ Keyboard clacks ]

07:38.192 --> 07:41.226
Detective Hudson
doesn't talk to anybody.

07:41.228 --> 07:44.029
When Sanchez comes in,
he sits and waits for a while.

07:44.031 --> 07:45.297
You didn't
take off your tie?

07:45.299 --> 07:47.966
Nothing happens
for a half an hour.

07:47.968 --> 07:49.134
Seemed longer.

07:49.136 --> 07:51.436
Tao: Julio goes up
to the bar,

07:51.438 --> 07:54.806
has the brief exchange with
our victim he told us about,

07:54.808 --> 07:56.274
and he leaves.

07:56.276 --> 07:59.778
And then, seven minutes later,
this woman enters.

07:59.780 --> 08:01.146
Sharon: Stop right there.
[ Keyboard clacks ]

08:01.148 --> 08:02.981
Can you enlarge her face,
Buzz?

08:02.983 --> 08:04.483
[ Keyboard clacking ]

08:05.085 --> 08:07.285
[ Computer dings, warbles ]

08:08.789 --> 08:11.523
Wow.
Look at that resolution.

08:11.525 --> 08:13.859
Detective Valdez,
do you recognize this woman?

08:13.861 --> 08:15.694
Could she be our Juliet?

08:16.497 --> 08:18.296
[ Exhales softly ]

08:21.802 --> 08:23.335
I have no idea.

08:23.904 --> 08:25.303
Tao: Okay, then.
Moving on.

08:25.305 --> 08:27.806
Madame X speaks
with Detective Hudson

08:27.808 --> 08:28.907
for about 20 minutes.

08:28.909 --> 08:30.275
Nothing unusual happens

08:30.277 --> 08:32.244
until he starts
getting ready to leave.

08:32.246 --> 08:37.215
And she gives him some sort
of -- an envelope, maybe?

08:37.217 --> 08:38.483
That envelope
wasn't on the body.

08:38.485 --> 08:40.719
This woman didn't
follow him out?

08:40.721 --> 08:42.654
Buzz: No.
The bartenders change shifts,

08:42.656 --> 08:44.422
and then she drinks
until last call.
[ Cellphone chimes ]

08:44.424 --> 08:46.892
Provenza: Hope she didn't
drive herself home.

08:46.894 --> 08:49.327
Um, Detective Valdez,
please forward

08:49.329 --> 08:52.898
all information relating to
the Bo McClaren investigation

08:52.900 --> 08:54.232
to Major Crimes.

08:54.234 --> 08:56.501
Everyone else, let's try
to identify this woman.

08:56.503 --> 08:57.702
Excuse me.

08:57.704 --> 08:59.304
[ Door opens ]

09:00.874 --> 09:04.209
[ Keyboard clacks,
computer dings ]

09:07.714 --> 09:09.214
[ Door opens ]

09:12.319 --> 09:14.119
[ Beck exhales sharply ]

09:14.121 --> 09:17.088
I'm -- I-I'm sorry.

09:17.090 --> 09:18.423
Uh...

09:19.726 --> 09:22.327
[ Door closes ]
I'm sorry to interrupt you
at work.

09:22.329 --> 09:25.263
I just -- I didn't want
to discuss it on the phone,

09:25.265 --> 09:27.465
and it affects our son.

09:30.571 --> 09:33.705
I'm sure we can
work something out.

09:33.707 --> 09:35.440
Have a seat, Sharon.

09:35.442 --> 09:37.208
Have a seat.

09:45.185 --> 09:47.285
So, um,
something happened

09:47.287 --> 09:50.155
when I was with Gary
last winter,

09:50.157 --> 09:52.757
something that I didn't
know about until later.

09:52.759 --> 09:55.760
And you're worried
it will affect your deal?

09:55.762 --> 09:56.828
No, it's not that.

09:56.830 --> 09:59.531
I, um...

09:59.533 --> 10:01.399
I'm pregnant.

10:02.636 --> 10:04.469
I'm about
four months along.

10:04.471 --> 10:07.105
Um,
it was a big surprise,

10:07.107 --> 10:08.907
and I didn't
mention it sooner

10:08.909 --> 10:12.110
because the doctor said
there was still a chance
that I could miscarry,

10:12.112 --> 10:16.514
but now it looks like
I'm doing really well, so...

10:17.651 --> 10:20.118
Sharon, that's, um...

10:20.120 --> 10:22.487
That's wonderful.

10:22.489 --> 10:24.389
Mm.

10:24.391 --> 10:26.024
I'm so glad
you feel that way.

10:26.026 --> 10:27.459
Mm.

10:27.461 --> 10:30.862
It's just, um, I don't know
what Rusty's gonna think,

10:30.864 --> 10:32.197
and I've gotten
to the point

10:32.199 --> 10:33.999
where I'm afraid
of his reactions to things.

10:34.001 --> 10:35.166
Mm.

10:35.168 --> 10:38.536
So, I was wondering if,
um...

10:38.538 --> 10:40.905
You would like<i> me</i>
to tell him?

10:40.907 --> 10:42.440
Would you?
Mm.

10:42.442 --> 10:44.809
Gary won't be involved
in the baby's life at all --

10:44.811 --> 10:46.177
or mine.

10:46.179 --> 10:49.214
And I just -- I'm just hoping
that Rusty sees this

10:49.216 --> 10:52.183
as an opportunity
to be a big brother,

10:52.185 --> 10:54.386
and that
he'll be happy about it.

10:55.222 --> 10:56.955
Yeah...he could be.

10:56.957 --> 11:00.058
Although I do think
he'll have some questions.

11:00.060 --> 11:02.093
Yeah.
He always has questions.

11:02.095 --> 11:05.563
Let's just hope
they're easier than usual.

11:06.366 --> 11:08.700
Bo:<i> Do you know what day</i>
<i> this is, Madeline?</i>

11:08.702 --> 11:11.970
<i> Tell us -- Why is this day</i>
<i> important to you?</i>

11:11.972 --> 11:13.838
<i> It's my birthday.</i>

11:13.840 --> 11:15.407
<i> See?</i>

11:15.409 --> 11:18.176
<i> 18 as of midnight.</i>

11:18.178 --> 11:20.645
<i> And how are you</i>
<i> gonna celebrate?</i>

11:31.358 --> 11:33.525
I think that's all we can
comfortably watch together.

11:33.527 --> 11:35.660
Speak for yourself.
I'm proud of my work.

11:35.662 --> 11:37.095
Although, of course,
this is unedited.

11:37.097 --> 11:38.563
We only shot it
four days ago.

11:38.565 --> 11:40.865
But I like to start my frequent
meetings at the L.A.P.D.

11:40.867 --> 11:43.334
with a demonstration
of how helpful I can be.

11:43.336 --> 11:46.037
So, in addition to coming in
without my lawyer,

11:46.039 --> 11:47.305
I like to do a little --

11:47.307 --> 11:49.140
it's called
a "show and tell."

11:49.142 --> 11:50.675
Be our guest.

11:50.677 --> 11:53.478
Now, forgive me if this part
seems over-rehearsed.

11:53.480 --> 11:55.647
I've just had to perform it
many, many times.

11:55.649 --> 11:58.883
18 and Out Entertainment
is a legitimate business

11:58.885 --> 12:01.953
<i> complying with every law --</i>
<i> state, federal, and municipal.</i>

12:01.955 --> 12:03.588
<i> Here you'll find</i>
<i> my tax information...</i>

12:03.590 --> 12:06.357
[ Lunchbox unzipping ]
<i> ...dating back to 2010,</i>

12:06.359 --> 12:09.160
<i> as I have be audited</i>
<i> every single year.</i>

12:09.996 --> 12:12.530
<i> These are records</i>
<i> of STD testing...</i>
Patrice's idea of my lunch.

12:12.532 --> 12:14.199
<i> ...required</i>
<i> of every performer</i>

12:14.201 --> 12:16.468
<i> before and during</i>
<i> each shoot.</i>

12:16.470 --> 12:18.169
<i> And here are our permits,</i>

12:18.171 --> 12:20.839
my business license,
our insurance policy,

12:20.841 --> 12:22.373
as well as...

12:22.375 --> 12:26.010
some customer reviews --
just for kicks.

12:26.012 --> 12:27.078
Reviews, huh?

12:27.080 --> 12:28.713
People love my work.

12:28.715 --> 12:31.850
Where do you find
your co-stars...
[ Sighs ]

12:31.852 --> 12:33.184
...the 18-year-old girls?

12:33.186 --> 12:35.053
These<i> women</i> find me,
Detective.

12:35.055 --> 12:36.287
They submit themselves,

12:36.289 --> 12:37.822
either through my website

12:37.824 --> 12:40.125
or one of our other
social-media platforms.

12:40.127 --> 12:42.794
<i> The porn industry isn't always</i>
<i> respectful to women.</i>

12:42.796 --> 12:43.828
<i> I am.</i>

12:43.830 --> 12:45.563
<i> I treat these women</i>
<i> as adults,</i>

12:45.565 --> 12:47.098
<i> which, legally, they are.</i>

12:47.100 --> 12:49.634
Were you with one of these
"adults" last night?

12:49.636 --> 12:51.236
No.

12:51.238 --> 12:53.838
I was home alone,
went to sleep around 9:00,

12:53.840 --> 12:54.739
woke up at 6:00.

12:54.741 --> 12:57.041
That's early to bed,
early to rise

12:57.043 --> 12:58.243
for an actor like you.

12:58.245 --> 12:59.644
Hey, series work
can be a grind.

12:59.646 --> 13:01.479
I need to look my best
for camera.

13:01.481 --> 13:02.747
You don't seem surprised

13:02.749 --> 13:04.616
that we're asking you
for an alibi.

13:04.618 --> 13:06.084
I'm used
to being on the shit-list

13:06.086 --> 13:07.385
of every cop
in the L.A.P.D.

13:07.387 --> 13:09.420
Including this guy's?

13:13.360 --> 13:15.994
Yes, including
Detective Hudson.

13:15.996 --> 13:17.529
He questioned me
a few times,

13:17.531 --> 13:19.564
sent city employees out
to check our permits,

13:19.566 --> 13:23.601
convince landlords it was
a health hazard to rent to us.

13:23.603 --> 13:26.070
A real jerk.

13:26.072 --> 13:27.272
Though, of course,

13:27.274 --> 13:29.240
condolences to his family
and all that.

13:29.242 --> 13:30.508
What happened to him?

13:30.510 --> 13:32.076
He was murdered last night
in a house

13:32.078 --> 13:34.579
with your company's name
on the lease agreement.

13:35.615 --> 13:37.148
I already told you
where I was.

13:37.150 --> 13:39.617
<i>I've installed security cameras</i>
<i> all around my duplex</i>

13:39.619 --> 13:42.253
<i> just so the L.A.P.D.</i>
<i> can confirm my whereabouts</i>

13:42.255 --> 13:43.655
<i> whenever necessary.</i>

13:43.657 --> 13:45.423
Flynn: Does anybody want
to watch any more video

13:45.425 --> 13:46.758
of this asshole?

13:46.760 --> 13:48.293
<i> Beyond that,</i>
<i> I don't know how I can help.</i>

13:48.295 --> 13:49.627
Not while I'm having
this fabulous lunch.

13:49.629 --> 13:52.831
Maybe, uh, patrol
can bring it in later.

13:52.833 --> 13:56.034
Sykes:
Do you know this woman?

14:01.041 --> 14:02.240
Yeah.
That's Lisa Cornell.

14:02.242 --> 14:04.108
<i> She's my producing partner.</i>
<i> Why?</i>

14:04.110 --> 14:05.844
Lieutenant. Mike.

14:05.846 --> 14:09.514
At least now
we know where she works.

14:09.516 --> 14:11.449
<i> Look, if this is --</i>
<i> if this is about murder,</i>

14:11.451 --> 14:13.117
<i> maybe I should get</i>
<i> my attorney involved.</i>

14:13.119 --> 14:14.552
You could.

14:14.554 --> 14:15.987
Though, I have to say,
that would bring an end

14:15.989 --> 14:19.657
to us looking at you
as being 100% cooperative.

14:19.659 --> 14:20.892
Sanchez: Well,
maybe you can tell us

14:20.894 --> 14:23.194
why we found
Detective Hudson dead

14:23.196 --> 14:24.996
in a house
rented by your company

14:24.998 --> 14:28.099
right after he was seen
having drinks with your partner.

14:28.101 --> 14:31.469
Lisa: I was trying to get him
to leave us alone.

14:31.471 --> 14:33.004
[ Exhales sharply ]

14:33.006 --> 14:36.908
I gave him $15,000 cash.
That's what was in the envelope.

14:36.910 --> 14:39.611
So, you paid off
Detective Hudson

14:39.613 --> 14:42.080
to get him to drop
his investigation

14:42.082 --> 14:43.548
into 18 and Out?
No!

14:43.550 --> 14:45.016
No,
I was trying to get him

14:45.018 --> 14:47.852
to stop selling drugs
to our performers.

14:47.854 --> 14:49.921
Drugs?
What kind of drugs?

14:49.923 --> 14:51.222
Meth, mostly.

14:51.224 --> 14:53.291
<i> But also X and Molly.</i>

14:53.293 --> 14:54.826
<i> Look, I'm a producer.</i>

14:54.828 --> 14:57.228
I also supervise the makeup
for all of Bo's co-stars.

14:57.230 --> 14:58.663
That close
to their faces,

14:58.665 --> 15:00.999
I could tell that
the girls were getting high.

15:01.001 --> 15:04.202
We are supposed to be
a completely drug-free set,

15:04.204 --> 15:05.737
no alcohol, even.

15:05.739 --> 15:08.973
But Drew kept coming around,
offering the girls great deals,

15:08.975 --> 15:10.675
<i> and not every payment</i>
<i> that he accepted</i>

15:10.677 --> 15:12.210
<i> was in cash, either.</i>

15:12.212 --> 15:13.811
Sharon: $15,000.

15:13.813 --> 15:16.915
You find any money
on Detective Hudson's body?

15:16.917 --> 15:17.849
Just a few 20s.

15:17.851 --> 15:19.450
But our friend Bo
over here

15:19.452 --> 15:22.186
didn't mention that
Hudson visited the sets.

15:22.188 --> 15:25.290
Well, he also failed to mention
the freely flowing meth.

15:25.292 --> 15:27.558
<i> Who would you people have</i>
<i> believed -- me or him?</i>

15:27.560 --> 15:29.627
Tao: Why pay him off
last night?

15:29.629 --> 15:30.995
Specifically,
what changed?

15:30.997 --> 15:36.401
The drugs -- They got
way too strong or tainted.

15:36.403 --> 15:37.902
[ Voice breaking ]
There were two girls --

15:37.904 --> 15:40.872
<i> Jodi Albertson</i>
<i> and Kim Murphy --</i>

15:40.874 --> 15:43.741
<i> they overdosed,</i>
<i> both of them.</i>

15:43.743 --> 15:45.109
<i> It was</i>
<i> after they left set,</i>

15:45.111 --> 15:49.113
but [Sobs] I think that
it finally dawned on Drew

15:49.115 --> 15:50.581
that he could
get caught,

15:50.583 --> 15:53.484
and I took the opportunity
to negotiate his departure.

15:53.486 --> 15:56.721
Buzz, contact Dr. Morales
and get some information

15:56.723 --> 15:59.924
on Jodi Albertson
and Kim Murphy, please.

15:59.926 --> 16:02.126
<i> I wasn't bribing</i>
<i> a police officer.</i>

16:02.128 --> 16:04.562
I was paying a drug dealer
to leave me alone.

16:04.564 --> 16:05.863
Is that
against the law?

16:05.865 --> 16:07.498
What did Bo
have to say about that?

16:07.500 --> 16:08.633
He doesn't know.

16:08.635 --> 16:10.468
And seeing as
it concerns drugs,

16:10.470 --> 16:11.970
he doesn't<i> want</i> to know.

16:11.972 --> 16:16.975
He won't notice $15,000 missing
from the accounts?

16:16.977 --> 16:18.676
Bo doesn't deal
with the bills.

16:18.678 --> 16:21.245
As he likes to tell it,
I'm the workhorse.

16:21.247 --> 16:22.513
He's the stud.

16:22.515 --> 16:24.382
The only number
that he cares about

16:24.384 --> 16:25.917
is how many women
that he's...

16:25.919 --> 16:29.854
[ Sighs ]
Well, you know.

16:31.891 --> 16:36.594
Any idea how Drew wound up dead
at one of your locations

16:36.596 --> 16:39.397
just a few hours
after<i> you</i> paid him off?

16:39.399 --> 16:40.798
Not a clue.

16:40.800 --> 16:44.435
In fact, just sitting there
and talking with him --

16:44.437 --> 16:45.870
it shook me up so badly

16:45.872 --> 16:49.707
that I -- I needed
to have a few drinks.

16:49.709 --> 16:51.075
Buzz: Uh, Captain?

16:51.077 --> 16:53.811
Uh, Dr. Morales says
that Jodi and Kim's bodies

16:53.813 --> 16:55.680
have already been released
to their families.

16:55.682 --> 16:59.017
He does, however, have
another young lady who
came in recently --

16:59.019 --> 17:02.153
same cause of death.

17:02.155 --> 17:05.289
Morales: Overdose from a mixture
of meth and antidepressants.

17:05.291 --> 17:09.394
Antidepressants are uppers
built to built energy and mood.

17:09.396 --> 17:10.595
Meth is an upper, too.

17:10.597 --> 17:12.597
So if you take
too much of both,

17:12.599 --> 17:14.565
your heart goes
into cardiac arrest.

17:14.567 --> 17:17.001
Her brother's in town now
from Salt Lake City

17:17.003 --> 17:18.703
waiting for us
to release her body.

17:18.705 --> 17:21.939
What about Jodi Albertson
and Kim Murphy?

17:21.941 --> 17:24.509
Overdose
on the same drug combo,

17:24.511 --> 17:28.913
which is how I was able to
identify the intoxicants in
this young girl so quickly,

17:28.915 --> 17:32.216
not that it's a particularly
rare form of substance abuse.

17:32.218 --> 17:33.951
Lots of teens being
treated for depression

17:33.953 --> 17:36.687
use meth without realizing
it messes with their heart.

17:36.689 --> 17:41.492
But the pattern here
is...striking.

17:41.494 --> 17:42.727
How so?

17:42.729 --> 17:45.663
The two previous girls,
like Madeline,

17:45.665 --> 17:48.099
died on or right after
their birthdays.

17:48.101 --> 17:51.436
<i> And</i> they were all
just 18.
Flynn: ...just 18.

17:51.438 --> 17:54.005
Yeah. We know.

17:54.007 --> 17:57.942
♪♪

18:05.118 --> 18:06.017
[ Static ]

18:06.019 --> 18:07.752
Rusty:
This security video

18:07.754 --> 18:10.488
from the ATM where your father
and uncle were killed,

18:10.490 --> 18:12.657
it'll be pretty gruesome,
Buzz.

18:12.659 --> 18:14.625
You want me
to watch it first?

18:16.696 --> 18:19.230
Also,
the official report says

18:19.232 --> 18:22.700
that the police reviewed
the tape, like, 100 times.

18:22.702 --> 18:24.969
Do you really think
that you might see
something they missed?

18:24.971 --> 18:28.039
No, but there have been a lot
of technological advances

18:28.041 --> 18:29.607
since 1986.

18:29.609 --> 18:31.109
I could digitize the video

18:31.111 --> 18:32.610
and run it
through some software

18:32.612 --> 18:35.146
designed to extrapolate
from still images,

18:35.148 --> 18:36.514
and that might give us

18:36.516 --> 18:40.218
a little something
to follow-up on.
[ VCR clicking ]

18:40.987 --> 18:41.853
[ Sighs ]

18:41.855 --> 18:43.788
This old VCR
is not working.

18:43.790 --> 18:45.323
Maybe Lieutenant Tao
can help you.

18:45.325 --> 18:46.524
This is my problem,

18:46.526 --> 18:48.292
and I am not bothering
Lieutenant Tao

18:48.294 --> 18:51.129
with some old case that doesn't
concern anyone else but me.

18:51.131 --> 18:53.131
I asked him one question
last week,

18:53.133 --> 18:54.031
and that's it.

18:54.033 --> 18:55.867
Y-yeah, no,
I-I understand

18:55.869 --> 18:58.769
not wanting
to ask anyone else for help.

18:58.771 --> 18:59.904
But we have a segment
of "Identity" to do, Buzz.

18:59.906 --> 19:01.606
So, how -- how long
do you think

19:01.608 --> 19:03.474
it's gonna take you
to fix all this?
[ Keypad beeping ]

19:03.476 --> 19:06.010
Or is there another part of
the story we could tell, maybe?

19:06.813 --> 19:09.113
Rusty, do you have minute?

19:09.115 --> 19:11.516
Uh, well, hopefully, I'm about
to record my next post.

19:11.518 --> 19:14.652
Oh, um, the, uh --
the communications department

19:14.654 --> 19:16.854
decided to stream "Identity"
on their website.

19:16.856 --> 19:19.590
Oh! That's wonderful.

19:19.592 --> 19:21.058
Will I see you
at home later?

19:21.060 --> 19:23.628
I was planning
to stay over at Gus' tonight

19:23.630 --> 19:25.062
while his roommate's
out of town. Why?

19:25.064 --> 19:27.498
Uh, Captain, we got
Madeline's death investigation

19:27.500 --> 19:28.599
from Beverly Hills.

19:28.601 --> 19:30.034
[ Exhales ] Um...

19:30.036 --> 19:31.802
What's -- what's going on?
Is everything okay?

19:31.804 --> 19:33.237
Nothing to worry about.

19:33.239 --> 19:34.605
Um, we'll talk tomorrow.

19:34.607 --> 19:36.240
Buzz, take your time.

19:36.242 --> 19:38.643
I'll let you know
if we need you.

19:42.215 --> 19:44.148
Mom says
you can take your time.

19:44.150 --> 19:46.817
I've taken 30 years.
Another day won't hurt me.

19:46.819 --> 19:48.853
Anyway, I can't let this
interfere with my job.

19:48.855 --> 19:50.188
But -- but
she -- she just said --

19:50.190 --> 19:52.657
Look, this may be
a story for you,

19:52.659 --> 19:53.991
but it's my life,

19:53.993 --> 19:56.360
and this is how
I have to get it done.

19:58.398 --> 20:01.799
[ Sighs ] Man.

20:01.801 --> 20:04.402
[ Exhales ]
Oh, the 20th century.

20:04.404 --> 20:06.604
Sykes: The detectives
from Beverly Hills PD

20:06.606 --> 20:10.007
treated Madeline Kimball's death
as an accidental overdose.

20:10.009 --> 20:12.643
But her hair samples were
negative for long-term abuse.

20:12.645 --> 20:14.345
She could have been
a first-time user,

20:14.347 --> 20:17.481
or she didn't
take the drugs willingly.

20:17.483 --> 20:20.184
Is there any connection between
Madeline and Detective Hudson?

20:20.186 --> 20:21.552
Uh, two, ma'am.

20:21.554 --> 20:24.322
First, her body was found
in a room at the Fontenot Hotel,

20:24.324 --> 20:26.123
where she'd been staying
for a month.

20:26.125 --> 20:28.359
And Bo McClaren
was footing the bill.

20:28.361 --> 20:29.894
Any other connection?

20:29.896 --> 20:32.163
Well, we got Madeline's phone
from Beverly Hills PD,

20:32.165 --> 20:35.032
and it's got both Bo
and Drew Hudson's names

20:35.034 --> 20:36.701
in her Snapchat contacts.

20:36.703 --> 20:37.935
Maybe Bo got jealous --

20:37.937 --> 20:39.537
killed Madeline,
then Drew Hudson.

20:39.539 --> 20:41.105
Uh, patrol e-mailed us

20:41.107 --> 20:42.940
security footage
from Bo's house.

20:42.942 --> 20:44.942
His alibi for Drew's murder
looks legitimate.

20:44.944 --> 20:47.144
He has
millions of dollars,

20:47.146 --> 20:49.981
so whether he just didn't like
being investigated,

20:49.983 --> 20:52.783
or our cop was moving in
on his girlfriend,

20:52.785 --> 20:55.486
he could have hired someone
to off Hudson.

20:55.488 --> 20:57.555
Well, either way, that's not
enough for a search warrant,

20:57.557 --> 20:59.190
so what do you want
to do now?

20:59.192 --> 21:02.493
Dr. Morales said that
Madeline's older brother is here

21:02.495 --> 21:03.794
waiting
to take her body home.

21:03.796 --> 21:05.329
Let's see what he knows.

21:05.331 --> 21:08.833
Nathan: Bo was the worst thing
that's ever happened to her.

21:08.835 --> 21:10.001
Let me show you.

21:10.003 --> 21:11.269
Before she met Bo,

21:11.271 --> 21:13.437
these were the types
of pictures she posted.

21:13.439 --> 21:17.008
And then that jerk started
talking to her online,

21:17.010 --> 21:19.710
encouraging her
to open a new account

21:19.712 --> 21:21.612
and post things
like this.

21:21.614 --> 21:22.880
Taylor:
He hasn't called a lawyer?

21:22.882 --> 21:24.282
Provenza:
He's not really a suspect.

21:24.284 --> 21:26.083
If his sister bought drugs
from a dirty cop,

21:26.085 --> 21:29.086
he has a civil suit against us
the size of our budget.

21:29.088 --> 21:31.389
Well, finding
Detective Hudson's killer

21:31.391 --> 21:32.823
is our first priority.

21:32.825 --> 21:34.659
Yes, but the money is
a very close second, though --

21:34.661 --> 21:35.993
extremely close.

21:35.995 --> 21:37.194
Flynn:<i> So, you think</i>
<i> all these photos</i>

21:37.196 --> 21:38.796
are the result
of Bo's influence?

21:38.798 --> 21:40.264
Of course they are.

21:40.266 --> 21:42.266
And they sent her Instagram
followers through the roof.

21:42.268 --> 21:46.103
Her pictures
got reposted everywhere.

21:46.105 --> 21:47.772
I always thought that
girls t-that needed

21:47.774 --> 21:49.140
this kind of attention

21:49.142 --> 21:50.875
came from broken homes
or whatever,

21:50.877 --> 21:53.444
but Madeline...

21:53.446 --> 21:55.379
Madeline was loved.

21:55.381 --> 21:57.782
And all it took
to ruin everything

21:57.784 --> 21:59.684
was Bo flying up
to see her.

21:59.686 --> 22:03.321
W-Wait. Bo McClaren went to
Salt Lake before she turned 18?

22:03.323 --> 22:04.355
Yeah.

22:04.357 --> 22:05.890
Yeah, and Madeline
didn't tell us.

22:05.892 --> 22:08.125
But I started following Bo
on Instagram, too,

22:08.127 --> 22:10.661
and he posted a picture
of her -- in person --

22:10.663 --> 22:12.463
<i> and then all these guys</i>

22:12.465 --> 22:14.732
<i> started making</i>
<i> disgusting comments on them.</i>

22:14.734 --> 22:16.033
[ Computer beeps ]
Tao: Yep.

22:16.035 --> 22:17.935
There's a post
geo-tagged in Salt Lake

22:17.937 --> 22:20.971
on Bo's Instagram account --
two months old.

22:20.973 --> 22:23.541
Caption reads,
"Scouting new talent in Utah.

22:23.543 --> 22:26.877
Can't wait to give Madeline
the ultimate birthday present."

22:26.879 --> 22:28.479
Did Madeline post this photo,
too?

22:28.481 --> 22:29.947
Did he send it to her?

22:29.949 --> 22:31.048
Uh, we can image-search
the picture

22:31.050 --> 22:32.416
and see where else
it turns up.

22:32.418 --> 22:34.385
<i> ...into thinking</i>
<i> that she was special,</i>

22:34.387 --> 22:37.788
to con her
into coming to L.A.

22:37.790 --> 22:39.256
When did Madeline
fly out?

22:39.258 --> 22:42.159
About a month ago,
right after graduation.

22:42.161 --> 22:43.361
Bo must have sent her
a ticket,

22:43.363 --> 22:44.962
because we didn't even know
she was gone

22:44.964 --> 22:46.664
until after she landed.

22:46.666 --> 22:49.867
I thought that that cop
that met her at the airport

22:49.869 --> 22:51.569
<i> might have changed her mind,</i>
<i> but --</i>

22:51.571 --> 22:52.803
What cop -- Hudson?

22:52.805 --> 22:54.238
Hudson met her
at the airport? Why?

22:54.240 --> 22:55.873
Could you panic more quietly,
please?

22:55.875 --> 22:57.074
We need to hear this.

22:57.076 --> 22:58.309
Flynn:<i> What do you mean,</i>

22:58.311 --> 22:59.977
<i> she met a cop</i>
<i> at the airport?</i>

22:59.979 --> 23:01.545
<i> What,</i>
<i> you guys didn't know?</i>

23:01.547 --> 23:03.514
<i> She said that there was</i>
<i> a detective from the L.A.P.D.</i>

23:03.516 --> 23:05.182
waiting for her
when she got off the plane.

23:05.184 --> 23:06.951
Did she mention
the officer's name?

23:06.953 --> 23:11.188
No. She thought that<i> I</i> called
the L.A.P.D. to bring her home,

23:11.190 --> 23:13.991
and -- and left me
this screaming voicemail.

23:13.993 --> 23:15.159
[ Computer beeps ]
There she is.

23:15.161 --> 23:16.494
<i> After that message...</i>
Oh, boy.

23:16.496 --> 23:18.362
<i> ...we didn't hear from her</i>
<i> for weeks.</i>

23:18.364 --> 23:19.830
Look at the name
on Madeline's new
Instagram account.

23:19.832 --> 23:22.299
"Juliet2yourRomeo."

23:22.301 --> 23:24.869
"Juliet" was the name
in Hudson's files
about Bo McClaren.

23:24.871 --> 23:27.071
Provenza: He wasn't
selling her drugs.

23:27.073 --> 23:28.906
He was using her
as a criminal informant.

23:28.908 --> 23:31.275
<i> ...waiting for</i>
<i> her birthday to...</i>
Taylor: Oh, God.

23:31.277 --> 23:33.544
He put he a minor
in this cesspool as a C.I.

23:33.546 --> 23:35.613
without protection,
and she died?

23:35.615 --> 23:38.749
Just when I thought things
couldn't get any worse.

23:38.751 --> 23:42.019
I have to loop the City Attorney
here on this right away.

23:42.021 --> 23:43.387
<i> I tried to tell her...</i>
[ Door opens ]

23:43.389 --> 23:44.655
<i> ...to reach out to that cop,</i>
<i> you know?</i>

23:44.657 --> 23:46.023
If Hudson was just trying

23:46.025 --> 23:48.025
to roll up Bo McClaren's
operations on his own

23:48.027 --> 23:49.260
using Madeline...

23:49.262 --> 23:52.363
Then he -- he took
his own vacation

23:52.365 --> 23:54.398
to find
Madeline's killer.

23:54.400 --> 23:56.267
He's not a dirty cop.

23:56.269 --> 23:59.136
No. But by going solo,
he got himself killed,

23:59.138 --> 24:00.671
and probably Madeline, too.

24:00.673 --> 24:02.039
Which is why we don't

24:02.041 --> 24:05.643
investigate
criminal suspects alone.

24:05.645 --> 24:12.416
Do you guys -- do you know
if she filmed anything yet?

24:12.985 --> 24:14.919
Oh, no.

24:14.921 --> 24:16.954
We can't let him
release that.

24:16.956 --> 24:19.957
I mean, she's dead!

24:19.959 --> 24:22.526
Surely he wouldn't
post that.

24:23.896 --> 24:25.162
Provenza:
I'm beginning to wonder

24:25.164 --> 24:27.798
about how low you can go,
Mr. McClaren.

24:27.800 --> 24:31.135
We know that you use girls
who mean nothing to you

24:31.137 --> 24:32.403
for financial gain.

24:32.405 --> 24:34.338
But apparently
you're scumbag enough

24:34.340 --> 24:36.974
to do it the ones
you care about, too.

24:36.976 --> 24:38.275
Can we skip the insults

24:38.277 --> 24:39.610
and just get
right to the questions?

24:39.612 --> 24:42.046
And you can address me,
not my client.

24:42.048 --> 24:45.449
He put Madeline up
in a fancy hotel,

24:45.451 --> 24:48.953
wined and dined her
more than his other "co-stars."

24:48.955 --> 24:50.821
So what?
Taking a girl out to dinner

24:50.823 --> 24:53.023
isn't against the law,
even in Utah.

24:53.025 --> 24:55.359
Why didn't he mention her
to us before?

24:55.361 --> 24:58.329
You were questioning Bo
about the death of Drew Hudson.

24:58.331 --> 25:01.165
Madeline's accidental overdose
never came up.

25:01.167 --> 25:02.900
We're not so sure
it was accidental.

25:02.902 --> 25:06.904
Maybe your client gave Madeline
an overdose, Charles,

25:06.906 --> 25:08.506
to shut her up.

25:08.508 --> 25:10.074
To shut her up?
What for?
Bo, not another word.

25:10.076 --> 25:12.009
You let them explain,
you let me respond.

25:12.011 --> 25:15.212
Madeline cozied up
to Detective Hudson

25:15.214 --> 25:19.283
by telling him about
you drugging teenage girls.

25:19.285 --> 25:22.253
<i> You had to keep her quiet,</i>
<i> and Hudson, too.</i>

25:22.255 --> 25:24.154
Does he seem
genuinely surprised?

25:24.156 --> 25:26.023
Don't forget,
he's an actor.

25:26.025 --> 25:27.558
Hardin:<i> This wasn't</i>
<i> about my client.</i>

25:27.560 --> 25:28.893
<i> He knew nothing</i>
<i> about the drugs -- Tell them.</i>

25:28.895 --> 25:30.194
I never bought drugs,

25:30.196 --> 25:31.729
never gave girls drugs.

25:31.731 --> 25:33.030
I'm not part
of that process.

25:33.032 --> 25:35.599
Tao:<i> Oh.</i>
<i> So now it's a "process."</i>

25:35.601 --> 25:37.568
I never touch drugs.

25:37.570 --> 25:40.104
No, you just knowingly
look the other way

25:40.106 --> 25:42.673
while three girls die.

25:42.675 --> 25:44.108
Three girls?! What?!

25:44.110 --> 25:45.676
Jodi Albertson,
Kim Murphy.

25:45.678 --> 25:48.579
They died
from the same batch of --
No, they did not!

25:48.581 --> 25:51.849
Jodi and Kim went back home
to Indiana and Idaho!

25:51.851 --> 25:55.619
They went to the morgue!

25:58.257 --> 26:00.858
Okay.
Lisa told me they'd left.

26:00.860 --> 26:02.226
She told me
they just went home.

26:02.228 --> 26:03.827
If somebody was getting
these girls drugs,

26:03.829 --> 26:05.029
it was Lisa, not me.

26:05.031 --> 26:08.098
Lisa --
your partner/makeup artist.

26:08.100 --> 26:09.733
Why was she giving
these girls drugs?

26:09.735 --> 26:13.037
Sometimes these gir--<i> women</i>
get stage fright, okay?

26:13.039 --> 26:15.906
Lisa used to act herself,
so she knows --
Hardin: Okay, that's it.

26:15.908 --> 26:17.274
Bo doesn't
take drugs himself,

26:17.276 --> 26:19.510
and he doesn't give drugs
to the girls, all right?

26:19.512 --> 26:23.213
If this is true, then Lisa
lied to us about everything.

26:23.215 --> 26:25.583
Maybe Lisa also lied
about the murder.

26:25.585 --> 26:28.152
Hardin:<i> ...Cope with being naked</i>
<i> on camera in different ways.</i>

26:28.154 --> 26:29.720
<i> And, as we all know,</i>

26:29.722 --> 26:32.289
if, uh, an actress develops
a case of nerves,

26:32.291 --> 26:33.557
production and scheduling

26:33.559 --> 26:35.526
demands that producers
help them out.

26:35.528 --> 26:38.896
"As we all know"?
Really?

26:38.898 --> 26:41.365
<i> ...And sets and locations</i>
<i> can be...</i>

26:41.367 --> 26:43.267
Excuse me.
<i> ...intimidating places</i>

26:43.269 --> 26:45.803
<i> for newcomers</i>
<i> making film debuts.</i>
[ Door closes ]

26:45.805 --> 26:47.371
[ Door opens ]

26:47.373 --> 26:48.606
Sharon: All right, Bo.

26:48.608 --> 26:50.240
If you weren't
personally involved

26:50.242 --> 26:51.609
in giving the girls drugs

26:51.611 --> 26:53.410
and you want to prove it,
call Lisa right now.

26:53.412 --> 26:56.447
Tell her you want to rush
and film something

26:56.449 --> 26:58.349
with a couple of new performers
tomorrow.

26:58.351 --> 27:03.621
And that your co-stars seem like
they might be very anxious.

27:03.623 --> 27:07.491
♪♪

27:16.235 --> 27:18.102
[ Rusty exhales softly ]
[ Door closes ]

27:19.805 --> 27:21.038
Hey!

27:21.040 --> 27:22.439
I thought you'd be at work
already.

27:22.441 --> 27:25.209
We set a trap last night
for our suspects,

27:25.211 --> 27:27.344
and then we need to see
if she takes the bait,

27:27.346 --> 27:30.080
which could happen
at any moment.

27:30.082 --> 27:34.718
So, why don't you
sit down for a sec?

27:34.720 --> 27:36.620
Okay.

27:36.622 --> 27:38.989
Uh, what's going on?

27:38.991 --> 27:40.624
Well...
[ Clears throat ]

27:40.626 --> 27:44.561
...your mother came
to visit me yesterday.

27:44.563 --> 27:45.562
Oh, no.

27:45.564 --> 27:48.399
Well,
it's not<i> exactly</i> negative.

27:48.401 --> 27:50.167
What's that
supposed to mean?

27:50.169 --> 27:54.238
It means
that she is pregnant,

27:54.240 --> 27:58.008
and, um, I'm afraid

27:58.010 --> 28:01.912
the father of the child
is Gary.

28:01.914 --> 28:04.248
This is real?

28:04.250 --> 28:05.416
She said this?

28:05.418 --> 28:06.884
Oh, my God.
[ Sighs ]

28:06.886 --> 28:09.720
I fully understand how this
could be upsetting for you.

28:09.722 --> 28:12.456
Oh, "upsetting"?
Sharon, this is not
just upsetting.

28:12.458 --> 28:15.059
And I don't even know what to
think about it myself, really.

28:15.061 --> 28:18.328
But your mother
is more stable.

28:18.330 --> 28:21.298
So, getting pregnant
with -- with Gary's child

28:21.300 --> 28:22.466
is more stable?

28:22.468 --> 28:23.834
Sharon, she has a job

28:23.836 --> 28:26.403
that doesn't even
pay her enough to make rent.

28:26.405 --> 28:28.005
She's house-sitting
at different apartments,

28:28.007 --> 28:30.908
and -- and right now is
the longest she has been sober

28:30.910 --> 28:32.242
since I was
6 years old.

28:32.244 --> 28:34.111
I see the challenges,

28:34.113 --> 28:39.783
and I also think about
how fragile people
in recovery can be.

28:39.785 --> 28:41.552
I think about that a lot.

28:41.554 --> 28:44.688
Yeah, but I -- I finally feel
like she was...
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

28:44.690 --> 28:46.857
...starting to get her life
back on track, and --

28:46.859 --> 28:50.260
Maybe it would help you to
stop thinking about your mother

28:50.262 --> 28:52.463
and focus on
what's best for the child.

28:52.465 --> 28:54.531
Lieutenant,
could you hold on a second?

28:54.533 --> 28:55.966
You're not
gonna like this either,

28:55.968 --> 28:59.069
but I told Sharon
that she could come here tonight

28:59.071 --> 29:00.370
to talk to you about it.

29:00.372 --> 29:02.339
Uh, she shouldn't
have this baby.

29:02.341 --> 29:05.809
That is your mother's choice,
young man.

29:05.811 --> 29:07.344
It's not yours.

29:11.083 --> 29:12.716
Yes, Lieutenant?

29:12.718 --> 29:15.853
On her way to meet Bo,

29:15.855 --> 29:21.325
our producer has made a pit stop
at a familiar location.

29:21.327 --> 29:22.593
Sharon: [ Through cellphone ]
All right.

29:22.595 --> 29:23.961
Let's hope we catch her
in the act.

29:23.963 --> 29:26.730
Oh, well, we're prepared
for her reaction.

29:26.732 --> 29:28.699
We'll call you back,
5 or 10.

29:28.701 --> 29:30.200
Thanks.

29:30.202 --> 29:32.436
[ Footsteps approaching ]

29:36.442 --> 29:37.674
[ Lisa clears throat ]

29:37.676 --> 29:38.742
Hi.

29:38.744 --> 29:40.978
I'm here to, uh, pick up
the to-go order.

29:44.416 --> 29:46.984
Now,<i> this</i> is odd.

29:46.986 --> 29:49.486
That you'd just walk up to a bar
at this hour,

29:49.488 --> 29:51.321
my old expert
on Internet dating here

29:51.323 --> 29:52.689
has an order
waiting for you.

29:52.691 --> 29:55.893
Uh, do you mind if we take
a look in that bag?

29:57.029 --> 29:58.529
Hey!

29:58.531 --> 30:00.464
We got a runner
headed outside!

30:03.335 --> 30:04.601
[ Panting ]

30:04.603 --> 30:07.070
L.A.P.D.
Stay still.

30:07.072 --> 30:10.140
In case you haven't figured
it out yet, Ms. Cornell,

30:10.142 --> 30:12.509
you're under arrest.

30:14.013 --> 30:16.046
Stop! L.A.P.D.!
Stop!

30:20.653 --> 30:21.885
Stop!

30:22.988 --> 30:24.855
[ Shouts indistinctly ]

30:29.395 --> 30:31.829
Don't move!
Get your hands up!

30:31.831 --> 30:33.630
[ Panting ]

30:33.632 --> 30:35.065
You have the right
to remain silent.

30:35.067 --> 30:36.934
Anything you say...
[ Handcuffs click ]

30:36.936 --> 30:38.769
...can and will be
used against you
in a court of law.

30:38.771 --> 30:40.070
You have the right
to an attorney.

30:40.072 --> 30:41.338
If you cannot
afford one,

30:41.340 --> 30:42.973
one will be appointed for you
by the state.

30:46.412 --> 30:47.578
[ Sighs ]

30:47.580 --> 30:49.479
Well,
that was unpleasant.

30:49.481 --> 30:51.081
Any luck?
No.

30:51.083 --> 30:53.483
Despite having his fingerprints
on a large bag of drugs

30:53.485 --> 30:54.918
and running
from the police,

30:54.920 --> 30:57.454
Brady the bartender
has denied any wrongdoing

30:57.456 --> 30:58.522
and invoked his rights.

30:58.524 --> 30:59.690
I've got him
on distribution,

30:59.692 --> 31:01.024
but nothing
on either murder.

31:01.026 --> 31:03.193
Unless, in the search
of his apartment,

31:03.195 --> 31:04.561
you guys found a knife

31:04.563 --> 31:06.897
matching up
to Detective Hudson's wounds,

31:06.899 --> 31:08.465
hopefully
with dried blood on it?

31:08.467 --> 31:10.634
No,
but we did find two keys

31:10.636 --> 31:13.303
belonging to the house
where Hudson was murdered.

31:13.305 --> 31:15.739
A location rented
by Bo's company,

31:15.741 --> 31:17.241
and Lisa said
she was in charge

31:17.243 --> 31:18.408
of all the business side
of things.

31:18.410 --> 31:20.277
<i> Two</i> keys?
Mm.

31:20.279 --> 31:22.512
It's helpful,
but still circumstantial.

31:22.514 --> 31:24.314
The most frustrating thing
about this...

31:24.316 --> 31:25.649
Mm?

31:25.651 --> 31:28.085
...is Bo McClaren
will walk out of here

31:28.087 --> 31:29.620
free as a lark.

31:29.622 --> 31:31.622
I'm not so sure
about that.

31:31.624 --> 31:32.856
Provenza:
We're not interested

31:32.858 --> 31:35.425
in hearing you say,
"I did it," Lisa,

31:35.427 --> 31:37.327
because that
we already know.

31:37.329 --> 31:38.896
We have two people --

31:38.898 --> 31:41.765
you and your buddy
Brady the bartender --

31:41.767 --> 31:43.567
and only one deal
to hand out.

31:43.569 --> 31:44.801
Gilman: Hilarious.

31:44.803 --> 31:46.703
Without Lisa's statement,
nothing says

31:46.705 --> 31:48.505
Detective Drew Hudson
wasn't selling drugs

31:48.507 --> 31:50.107
<i> on the 18 and Out sets,</i>
<i> too.</i>

31:50.109 --> 31:52.876
Except her business partner
who's already given her up.

31:52.878 --> 31:55.045
<i> Oh, and by the way --</i>
<i> It occurs to me</i>

31:55.047 --> 31:57.147
<i> that the family</i>
<i> of this Madeline girl</i>

31:57.149 --> 32:00.083
<i> could end up with a big, fat</i>
<i> lawsuit against the L.A.P.D.</i>

32:00.085 --> 32:01.752
<i> no matter what</i>
<i> was going on.</i>

32:01.754 --> 32:04.421
So, instead of walking in here
and saying, "Boo,"

32:04.423 --> 32:05.756
why not make us
a reasonable offer?

32:05.758 --> 32:08.525
Okay, how about
I prosecute Lisa

32:08.527 --> 32:09.993
for two murders
instead of four?

32:09.995 --> 32:12.396
Excuse me?
Wait, what?! Four?!

32:12.398 --> 32:14.197
Uh, you remember
Jodi and Kim --

32:14.199 --> 32:17.501
the girls that you were
so weepy about yesterday?

32:17.503 --> 32:19.569
They overdosed
on your drugs.

32:19.571 --> 32:21.204
<i> Four</i> murders?

32:21.206 --> 32:24.274
Look, those young women
took the drugs themselves.

32:24.276 --> 32:25.642
They misused them.

32:25.644 --> 32:27.678
And Lisa has
an unbreakable alibi

32:27.680 --> 32:28.879
for when your cop
was murdered.

32:28.881 --> 32:31.081
Yes.
She met Drew at the hotel

32:31.083 --> 32:34.384
so that you could
get your alibi on camera.

32:34.386 --> 32:35.986
Brady was
finishing his shift.

32:35.988 --> 32:39.456
As I settled my tab, he left
while you and Drew were talking.

32:39.458 --> 32:41.591
And Brady had a key
to the location

32:41.593 --> 32:43.627
where Detective Hudson
was stabbed to death --

32:43.629 --> 32:45.529
a location rented
by you.

32:45.531 --> 32:48.332
Do you know why
you're so worried?

32:48.334 --> 32:51.001
Because you know Brady
and you know how scared he is.

32:51.003 --> 32:53.704
He ran off, and he left you
holding the bag!

32:53.706 --> 32:55.973
If you don't talk to us,
he will!

32:55.975 --> 32:57.207
And at trial, the way

32:57.209 --> 33:00.577
you help vulnerable teens
with their stage fright

33:00.579 --> 33:03.613
will be carefully explained
to the jury.

33:03.615 --> 33:04.748
And they won't like that.

33:04.750 --> 33:06.149
It makes the death penalty

33:06.151 --> 33:08.085
sound like
a public service.
Hobbs: Yeah.

33:08.087 --> 33:10.787
We have special circumstances
wherever you look --

33:10.789 --> 33:13.557
double homicide,
lying in wait.

33:13.559 --> 33:15.993
What was the other one?
Oh, I know -- killing a cop.

33:15.995 --> 33:18.362
I didn't kill him!
I was at the bar! I d--

33:18.364 --> 33:19.796
You didn't swing the ax,

33:19.798 --> 33:22.766
but you placed Detective
Hudson's head on the block...

33:22.768 --> 33:25.135
Oh!
...and that is good enough
for Murder One.

33:25.137 --> 33:26.503
So, you're gonna tell me

33:26.505 --> 33:28.538
everything I want to know
right now,

33:28.540 --> 33:30.207
<i> or I'm moving on</i>
<i> to run-away Brady</i>

33:30.209 --> 33:32.509
<i> and you can take your chances</i>
<i> in court.</i>

33:34.346 --> 33:36.213
<i> [ Whispering ]</i>

33:36.215 --> 33:37.681
Come on, Lisa.

33:37.683 --> 33:39.316
Give me what I need.

33:39.318 --> 33:41.051
Give me what I need.

33:44.089 --> 33:46.790
No murder charges,
no consecutive sentences.

33:46.792 --> 33:48.825
We take the max
on manslaughter

33:48.827 --> 33:50.794
and possession
with intent to distribute,

33:50.796 --> 33:52.863
all served concurrently --
nothing else.

33:52.865 --> 33:55.265
That depends on what
her hypothetical statement

33:55.267 --> 33:57.501
sounds like.

34:01.907 --> 34:05.976
<i> I-I never gave meth</i>
<i>to anybody that didn't want it.</i>

34:05.978 --> 34:08.011
<i> And -- and Bo was pleased</i>

34:08.013 --> 34:10.347
<i> that the scenes</i>
<i> were going more smoothly,</i>

34:10.349 --> 34:14.017
and that his -- his co-stars,
they seemed less inhibited.

34:14.019 --> 34:17.020
<i> But sometimes</i>
<i> for -- for these girls,</i>

34:17.022 --> 34:19.189
<i> the crash</i>
<i> can be really hard.</i>
Thank you, Lisa.

34:19.191 --> 34:21.391
That was<i> very</i> helpful.

34:21.393 --> 34:23.460
So, Brady read
on the Internet

34:23.462 --> 34:24.995
that antidepressants
can help

34:24.997 --> 34:26.730
to ease the come-down
from the meth.

34:26.732 --> 34:29.066
So you gave them
to Jodi and Kim?

34:29.068 --> 34:30.767
Look,
I'm not a doctor, okay?

34:30.769 --> 34:32.402
I didn't know that
you can't mix these things!

34:32.404 --> 34:33.904
And then, of course,

34:33.906 --> 34:36.873
the motel maids find
Jodi and Kim, not me.

34:36.875 --> 34:39.242
I-I didn't even know
that they were dead

34:39.244 --> 34:41.745
for a couple of days.

34:41.747 --> 34:43.780
What happened
with Madeline?

34:43.782 --> 34:45.715
It was her birthday,

34:45.717 --> 34:48.051
and I could tell
that she was anxious,

34:48.053 --> 34:50.187
so I just offered her
a little bump.

34:50.189 --> 34:53.590
And just --
she just couldn't handle it.

34:53.592 --> 34:56.393
I guess she just didn't
have a tolerance,

34:56.395 --> 34:58.128
and she went
from zero to 60,

34:58.130 --> 34:59.196
and she just kept saying,

34:59.198 --> 35:01.231
"Oh, my God,
it's happening to me!

35:01.233 --> 35:03.900
It's happening to me,
just like it happened
to Jodi and Kim!"

35:03.902 --> 35:06.636
Only she had never even met
Jodi or Kim!

35:06.638 --> 35:08.105
So that's
how you learned

35:08.107 --> 35:11.241
that Madeline was talking
to Detective Hudson.

35:11.243 --> 35:14.845
I had no idea the police
were investigating anything

35:14.847 --> 35:16.413
until that moment.

35:16.415 --> 35:19.349
And -- and Madeline
was so messed up that I...

35:21.987 --> 35:23.820
...I had to drive her
back to the hotel.

35:23.822 --> 35:26.156
Where you handed her off
to Brady,

35:26.158 --> 35:28.592
and you told him
that she was an informant!

35:28.594 --> 35:30.093
I didn't know
that he was gonna

35:30.095 --> 35:32.129
deliberately gonna give her
those antidepressants!

35:32.131 --> 35:34.865
<i> And</i> she was friends
with that cop!

35:34.867 --> 35:36.166
Provenza: "That cop"?

35:36.168 --> 35:39.703
That cop's name was
Detective Drew Hudson.

35:39.705 --> 35:43.940
Now, when Madeline died,
Detective Hudson...

35:43.942 --> 35:46.510
I thought that
he was going to kill me.

35:46.512 --> 35:49.546
I guess that he had been
in daily contact with Madeline,

35:49.548 --> 35:51.181
and he was convinced

35:51.183 --> 35:53.884
that she was going to help him
arrest Bo for drug dealing,

35:53.886 --> 35:56.019
at least,
that's what he told me.

35:56.021 --> 35:58.622
And Detective Hudson
explained to me

35:58.624 --> 36:00.957
that he was
working the case alone,

36:00.959 --> 36:03.059
<i> and that if I helped him</i>
<i> to get Bo --</i>

36:03.061 --> 36:05.395
Sanchez:<i> Then he'd find a way</i>
<i> to keep you out of it.</i>

36:05.397 --> 36:08.131
<i> So you set up a meeting</i>
<i> with Hudson at the bar,</i>

36:08.133 --> 36:10.167
lied to him --
told him what?

36:11.303 --> 36:13.570
That there were drugs
hidden at the location

36:13.572 --> 36:16.773
in a bag
with Bo's prints on it.

36:16.775 --> 36:21.278
A-And, yes, I gave him
the key to the house.

36:21.280 --> 36:23.380
But, look, uh,
this whole thing --

36:23.382 --> 36:26.383
This was all Brady's plan.
I argued against it.

36:31.423 --> 36:32.989
She says all this
in court

36:32.991 --> 36:35.926
before we arrest Brady
on these charges

36:35.928 --> 36:37.561
so she can't
take it back,

36:37.563 --> 36:42.399
and I give her one count
of Murder Two,

36:42.401 --> 36:45.001
and one count
of Conspiracy to Commit Murder.
[ Breathes shakily ]

36:45.003 --> 36:46.536
Wait, wait!
We were talking about --

36:46.538 --> 36:47.704
That's what it's gonna be,
Gilman,

36:47.706 --> 36:49.806
or I'll get what I need
from Brady

36:49.808 --> 36:52.676
and you can take her statement
and shove it up your ass.

36:53.412 --> 36:55.845
Sanchez:<i> That's</i>
<i> a double-homicide with a cop!</i>

36:55.847 --> 36:57.714
So, the bartender and
the makeup artist go to jail,

36:57.716 --> 37:00.417
and the sexual predator --
he goes free.

37:00.419 --> 37:02.285
We'll see.

37:02.287 --> 37:04.621
Provenza:<i> And you do</i> not
<i> want a jury...</i>

37:04.623 --> 37:05.922
We'll see.

37:05.924 --> 37:09.092
<i> ...to pass judgment</i>
<i> on your life.</i>

37:14.132 --> 37:16.199
Uh, Captain, I just spoke
to Madeline's brother.

37:16.201 --> 37:18.368
In return
for his family not suing us,

37:18.370 --> 37:21.171
he wants to make sure
all of Bo McClaren's video

37:21.173 --> 37:23.506
featuring his little sister
is destroyed.

37:23.508 --> 37:25.108
You think that's doable?

37:25.110 --> 37:27.744
Very doable,
and that also allows you

37:27.746 --> 37:29.546
to treat
Detective Hudson's death

37:29.548 --> 37:33.683
as a tragedy for the L.A.P.D.
and for his family.

37:33.685 --> 37:36.886
Which it is, yes.
Which it is.

37:36.888 --> 37:39.356
McClaren and his attorney
are waiting with Flynn

37:39.358 --> 37:40.724
by the elevator.

37:40.726 --> 37:43.059
I'll go and ask them
for the video, then.

37:43.061 --> 37:45.161
Oh, no.<i> I'll</i> talk to them.
Um, Amy?

37:45.163 --> 37:46.696
And we're not going
to ask for anything.

37:46.698 --> 37:48.298
Come on.
Come on.

37:48.300 --> 37:51.901
♪♪

37:51.903 --> 37:55.038
Uh, Lieutenant?

37:55.040 --> 37:58.208
I'm having a problem with
getting this old VCR to work,

37:58.210 --> 37:59.909
and if it's not too much
trouble, I was --

37:59.911 --> 38:01.244
Let me take a look
at it.

38:01.246 --> 38:03.380
Sanchez: My mom still has
a VCR, Buzz.

38:03.382 --> 38:04.581
I may be able to help you.

38:04.583 --> 38:06.149
[ Stammers ]
Uh, okay, thank you.

38:06.151 --> 38:08.752
Provenza: If you figure out how
to program one of those things

38:08.754 --> 38:12.055
so that it actually
records a show

38:12.057 --> 38:14.624
while you're having dinner,
let me know.

38:14.626 --> 38:17.727
[ Scoffs ]

38:17.729 --> 38:20.597
Another $300
I could have spent drinking.

38:20.599 --> 38:24.501
♪♪

38:32.110 --> 38:34.778
Oh, my God. I thought
all this bullshit was over.

38:34.780 --> 38:36.146
It is.
You're under arrest

38:36.148 --> 38:37.914
for I-don't-know-how-many
counts of rape.

38:37.916 --> 38:39.115
Excuse me?
Rape? What?

38:39.117 --> 38:40.450
I've never raped anyone
in my --

38:40.452 --> 38:41.718
Are you kidding me?

38:41.720 --> 38:43.353
Women submit applications
to sleep with me.

38:43.355 --> 38:45.121
You've made that
very clear to us,

38:45.123 --> 38:47.023
and also that
<i> you</i> don't use drugs.

38:47.025 --> 38:48.391
He doesn't.
Test him.

38:48.393 --> 38:51.161
But the girls he had sex with
used drugs.

38:52.531 --> 38:54.164
Okay, so, some of the girls
used drugs.

38:54.166 --> 38:56.199
How is that<i> my</i> problem?

38:56.201 --> 38:58.868
Oh, my God.
"Oh, my God" is right.

38:58.870 --> 39:00.103
What?
What is it?

39:00.105 --> 39:01.705
Flynn: If you knew
the girls were high,

39:01.707 --> 39:02.806
they couldn't
give their consent

39:02.808 --> 39:04.574
for sex with you,
asshole.

39:04.576 --> 39:06.943
And you told us Lisa
was drugging these girls.

39:06.945 --> 39:09.079
And you just admitted
you knew it -- again.

39:09.081 --> 39:12.649
Thank you for filming
all of your sexual assaults.

39:12.651 --> 39:14.751
Taylor: We'll be confiscating
your video for trial.

39:14.753 --> 39:16.286
[ Elevator dings ]
What?

39:16.288 --> 39:18.254
Charles, you cannot let this
happen to me!

39:18.256 --> 39:20.023
This is complete bullshit!
Sykes: Let's go!

39:20.025 --> 39:22.325
I'd never rape --
Rape? Are you serious?!

39:22.327 --> 39:23.460
Shut up!

39:23.462 --> 39:25.261
[ Elevator doors close ]

39:25.263 --> 39:27.497
Hey, Sharon.

39:27.499 --> 39:28.898
Your moral values aside,

39:28.900 --> 39:30.767
these girls only got
what they asked for.

39:30.769 --> 39:31.901
Really?

39:31.903 --> 39:34.037
The meth took away
their ability

39:34.039 --> 39:36.439
to properly understand
their actions.

39:36.441 --> 39:38.108
When it comes to sex,

39:38.110 --> 39:41.044
<i> who</i> properly understands
their actions?

39:41.046 --> 39:44.547
Beck: I didn't exactly plan
on having you, either.

39:46.017 --> 39:48.351
Was that a mistake?

39:48.353 --> 39:52.122
Look, I admit
that your life was hard.

39:52.124 --> 39:54.124
But you turned out okay.

39:54.126 --> 39:56.793
Mom, the only reason
we are even here,

39:56.795 --> 39:58.094
having this conversation,

39:58.096 --> 40:00.163
is because I witnessed
a murder victim

40:00.165 --> 40:02.532
being buried
in Griffith Park.

40:02.534 --> 40:05.034
Are -- are you planing on
arranging something like that

40:05.036 --> 40:06.569
for your next kid, too?

40:09.941 --> 40:11.708
Well,
I can't have an abortion.

40:11.710 --> 40:13.076
I'm too far along.

40:13.078 --> 40:15.145
I'm -- I'm not even
suggesting that, Mom.

40:15.147 --> 40:16.346
Well,
what are you suggesting,

40:16.348 --> 40:18.281
besides that
I'm a terrible person

40:18.283 --> 40:20.049
with no ability
to change?

40:20.051 --> 40:22.852
That you have the baby,
Mom,

40:22.854 --> 40:24.954
but you put it
up for adoption

40:24.956 --> 40:26.523
so that the child has

40:26.525 --> 40:30.326
a decent chance
at a normal life.

40:33.932 --> 40:36.566
[ Sighs ]

40:37.569 --> 40:40.503
I won't hold anything
that you just said...

40:40.505 --> 40:41.671
[ Swallows ]

40:41.673 --> 40:43.173
...against you, Rusty.

40:43.175 --> 40:46.376
Because I know
I've done terrible things

40:46.378 --> 40:51.047
and Gary did
terrible things.

40:51.049 --> 40:56.319
But I -- I can't do this
all on my own.

40:56.321 --> 41:00.056
So, if you can't support me --
even a little bit --

41:00.058 --> 41:07.030
then...I might have to let
someone else have my baby.

41:07.032 --> 41:08.731
[ Exhales sharply ]

41:08.733 --> 41:11.668
I will think about
everything that you said...

41:13.738 --> 41:16.406
...and you think about it,
too.

41:16.408 --> 41:17.707
Okay?

41:17.709 --> 41:21.678
♪♪

41:26.084 --> 41:28.384
[ Door opens ]
[ Sighs ]

41:34.359 --> 41:37.026
[ Sighs ]

41:39.664 --> 41:43.566
♪♪
